line_infer example


contains example that the slope and intercept of a line from noisy data using
Bayesâ€™ rule. The C++ libraries are called directly from the driver program.
By changing the likelihood function and the input data, this program can be
tailored to other inference problems.

For more information, look in UQTk manual under
Bayesian Inference of a Line

================================================================================
Files

line_infer.py: main scripts, run this program to run the example

line_infer.cpp: C++ code that produces some of the needed functions

line_infer.xml.templ: template for the xml file needed to run example

model.h
posterior.h
XMLreader.h
